The Attorney-General of the Federation (AGF) and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami has faulted reports that his office conclusively exonerated Abba Kyari. Malami, in a statement on Sunday by his media aide, Dr. Umar Jibrilu Gwandu, said “there appears to be misunderstanding regarding the issue. “It was a case of work in progress in respect of which the office of the Attorney General of the Federation requested for further probe in relation to some aspects of the investigation.   Lekki deep seaport to commence activities September –…     NSCDC arrests 19 suspects in possession of illegally refined…     Olubadan to Buratai: I’ll be meeting Ibadan title holders…   “It was clear that the conclusion on the alleged contradiction on the issue was a clear case of  misconception. “The office of the Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice’s stance is that no conclusion has been reached in the direction of absence of evidence relating to the first report. “The issues were raised  for further investigation with a view to covering the field in the investigation in order to arrived at an informed decision,” he said.